      • newInstance

        public static DeviceSelectorDialog newInstance(MediaBrowserCompat mediaBrowser)
        Creates a new DeviceSelectorDialog. This is the only way a DeviceSelectorDialog should be created. If creation is not done through this method the DeviceSelectorDialog will be unable to communicate with the MoppyMediaService and will be effectively useless.
        Parameters:
        mediaBrowser - the MediaBrowserCompat used to communicate with the MoppyMediaService
        Returns:
        the created DeviceSelectorDialog

      • onUsbPermissionIntent

        public void onUsbPermissionIntent(Intent intent)
        Handles device connection when permission had to be requested first. MUST be called when a MainActivity.ACTION_USB_PERMISSION broadcast is handled by MainActivity's BroadcastReceiver.
        Parameters:
        intent - the intent associated with the ACTION_USB_PERMISSION broadcast

      • onDeviceConnectionStateChanged

        public void onDeviceConnectionStateChanged()
        Updates this DeviceSelectorDialog's available device lists if it is showing, otherwise waits for the next time this DeviceSelectorDialog is shown to refresh. Should be called when either UsbManager.ACTION_USB_DEVICE_ATTACHED or UsbManager.ACTION_USB_DEVICE_DETACHED occurs.
